Southeast and business community representative in the Police Service Commission (PSC) Dr Jumbo Nkemka Offor is dead, according to TheNation. It was gathered that Offor died Wednesday night at his Enugu home, Osimiri Lodge. Details on the cause of his death were yet to be disclosed. A medical doctor by training, Offor who hailed from Arochukwu in Abia state ventured into the world of business immediately after graduation. He was the president, Enugu Chamber of Commerce, Industry, Mines and Agriculture (ECCIMA). He also coordinated the Enugu zone of Nigeria ’99 World Youth Soccer fiesta. Source •Sir Emeka Offor By Stanley NwanosikeENUGU - The Enugu Electricity Distribution Company (EEDC) has commended Sir Emeka Offor, Chairman of Chrome Group, for his philanthropic contributions to end polio in Nigeria.  The Head, Communications of EEDC, Mr Emeka Ezeh, gave the commendation in a statement made available to News Agency… July 22, 2019 In "Top Stories" By Stanley Nwanosike ENUGU -  Nigeria’s Polio Ambassador, Sir Emeka Offor, has donated N8.52million to the Department of Clinical Pharmacy, University of Nigeria, Nsukka (UNN), towards furnishing and up-grading of its Digital Anatomy Laboratory. Head of Communications of Enugu Electricity Distribution Company (EEDC), Mr. Emeka Ezeh, made this known in… August 17, 2019 In "Education" DESPITE its success in the last elections across the country, the All Progressive congress (APC) is not in a comfortable zone in Enugu State and from all indications; it appears that the party is not yet ready to dominate the political space. For a political party that has just won… May 19, 2015 In "Politics"